Android Studio How-To!

How to checkout:
Open Android Studio and select Check out from Version Control and select GitHub.
Log in using your GitHub credentials.
Choose to use Gradle to import.
Use auto-import and default gradle wrapper.
You now have the project in the IDE!

How to commit your changes:
After testing so that the new functions work, press Ctrl-K.
Add a comment describing what you have changed.
Press Commit (or Commit and Push if you want to push instantly).
Now push the changes to GitHub, and we can all use the new functions!
